<h1>Free AI Business Tools 2026: Best No-Cost Options</h1>

<p><em>Last updated: June 2026</em></p>

<p>Running a business in 2026 means managing sales pipelines, generating leads, taking meeting notes, and following up with prospects — all while keeping costs under control. Fortunately, a new wave of AI-powered business tools offers genuinely useful free tiers that can replace expensive enterprise software.</p>

<p>In this guide, we compare the best free AI business tools for sales, CRM, and operations. Whether you're a solopreneur, a small business owner, or part of a growing team, these tools will help you work smarter without adding to your monthly bills.</p>

<h2>1. HubSpot AI (Free) — Best Free CRM with AI Features</h2>
<p><strong>Rating: 4.5/5</strong></p>
<p>HubSpot's free CRM is the gold standard for free business tools, combining contact management, deal tracking, and email scheduling at no cost. The free tier supports unlimited users and up to 1 million contacts, making it incredibly generous compared to any competitor. Its AI assistant helps draft emails, generate meeting notes, and suggest next-best actions with leads based on your sales history. HubSpot also includes live chat, ticketing, and a customizable dashboard — all without requiring a credit card. For any small business looking to professionalize their sales process, HubSpot's free CRM is the obvious starting point.</p>
<p><strong>Free tier:</strong> Unlimited users, up to 1M contacts, AI assistant, live chat<br/>
<strong>Best for:</strong> CRM, deal tracking, email scheduling, sales automation<br/>
<strong>Limits:</strong> No custom reporting, limited automation workflows</p>
<p><a href="/tool/hubspot-ai" class="btn-primary">View HubSpot Free Tier →</a></p>

<h2>2. Apollo (Free) — Best Lead Generation & Sales Intelligence</h2>
<p><strong>Rating: 4.4/5</strong></p>
<p>Apollo delivers 10,000 free credits per month on its generous free tier, giving you access to over 275 million B2B contacts with advanced filtering options. The AI-powered lead scoring helps prioritize the most promising prospects based on your ideal customer profile and past conversion data. Apollo's free plan also includes email sequencing, automated follow-ups, and LinkedIn integration for seamless prospecting. You can build targeted contact lists by industry, company size, job title, and technology stack. It's essentially a full sales intelligence platform at no cost — a game-changer for bootstrapped sales teams.</p>
<p><strong>Free tier:</strong> 10,000 credits/month, B2B contact database, email sequences<br/>
<strong>Best for:</strong> Lead generation, prospecting, sales intelligence<br/>
<strong>Limits:</strong> Credits reset monthly, limited team seats</p>
<p><a href="/tool/apollo" class="btn-primary">View Apollo Free Tier →</a></p>

<h2>3. Fireflies (Free) — Best AI Meeting Transcription</h2>
<p><strong>Rating: 4.4/5</strong></p>
<p>Fireflies provides unlimited recording on its free tier, which is remarkable for a meeting transcription tool. It automatically joins your Google Meet, Zoom, Microsoft Teams, and Webex calls to capture every word without manual intervention. The AI generates searchable transcripts, concise meeting summaries, and action items that integrate with your CRM and project management tools. Fireflies also offers conversational intelligence features like speaker talk time analysis and sentiment tracking. It eliminates the need for manual note-taking across all your business meetings, ensuring nothing falls through the cracks.</p>
<p><strong>Free tier:</strong> Unlimited recording, searchable transcripts, AI summaries<br/>
<strong>Best for:</strong> Meeting transcription, note-taking, action item tracking<br/>
<strong>Limits:</strong> Limited storage, no advanced analytics</p>
<p><a href="/tool/fireflies" class="btn-primary">View Fireflies Free Tier →</a></p>

<h2>4. Otter (Free) — Best Real-Time Meeting Transcription</h2>
<p><strong>Rating: 4.4/5</strong></p>
<p>Otter offers 300 minutes of free transcription per month with its AI meeting assistant that joins and transcribes virtual meetings in real time. The free tier includes automated slide capture that syncs transcript text with presentation visuals for easy reference. Otter's speaker identification keeps track of who said what, and its keyword extraction highlights important topics discussed. Shareable summaries keep team members who missed the meeting fully in the loop. For teams with moderate meeting volumes, Otter's free tier is a practical and polished choice.</p>
<p><strong>Free tier:</strong> 300 min/month transcription, real-time captioning, slide capture<br/>
<strong>Best for:</strong> Meeting transcription, real-time collaboration, summaries<br/>
<strong>Limits:</strong> 300 min/month cap, no Salesforce integration</p>
<p><a href="/tool/otter" class="btn-primary">View Otter Free Tier →</a></p>

<h2>5. Salesloft (Free) — Best Sales Engagement Platform</h2>
<p><strong>Rating: 4.3/5</strong></p>
<p>Salesloft provides a free tier with basic sales engagement features that help solo sellers manage outreach at scale. You can create email cadences, track opens and clicks, and automate follow-up sequences to stay top-of-mind with prospects. The platform uses AI to suggest optimal send times based on recipient behavior patterns, increasing reply rates. Salesloft's free plan includes basic analytics to measure engagement performance across your campaigns. It's a solid entry-level option for individual sellers or very small teams testing sales engagement automation before upgrading.</p>
<p><strong>Free tier:</strong> Basic cadences, email tracking, open/click analytics<br/>
<strong>Best for:</strong> Sales engagement, email cadences, outreach automation<br/>
<strong>Limits:</strong> Limited to single user, no advanced analytics</p>
<p><a href="/tool/salesloft" class="btn-primary">View Salesloft Free Tier →</a></p>

<h2>6. Lusha (Free) — Best B2B Contact Data</h2>
<p><strong>Rating: 4.3/5</strong></p>
<p>Lusha offers 5 free credits per month for accessing verified B2B contact data, including phone numbers and email addresses. The free tier works as a browser extension that integrates seamlessly with LinkedIn, Salesforce, and HubSpot for one-click prospecting. Lusha's AI enrichment fills in missing contact details from minimal input — a company name and title is often enough to generate a match. The platform maintains high data accuracy through continuous verification against multiple sources. While the credit limit is low, Lusha is invaluable for occasional prospecting needs or validating key contacts.</p>
<p><strong>Free tier:</strong> 5 credits/month, browser extension, LinkedIn integration<br/>
<strong>Best for:</strong> Contact enrichment, prospecting, data verification<br/>
<strong>Limits:</strong> Only 5 credits/month, no API access</p>
<p><a href="/tool/lusha" class="btn-primary">View Lusha Free Tier →</a></p>

<h2>7. Lemlist (Free Trial) — Best AI Cold Email Outreach</h2>
<p><strong>Rating: 4.2/5</strong></p>
<p>Lemlist offers a free trial rather than a permanent free tier, giving you time to test its AI-powered cold email platform. The trial includes access to image-based personalization that dynamically inserts prospect-specific visuals into email campaigns to boost reply rates. Lemlist's AI helps craft subject lines and body copy optimized for cold outreach based on industry best practices and A/B test data. The platform includes automated follow-up sequences, spam score checks, and deliverability optimization. It's worth testing for businesses building outbound email strategies before committing to a paid plan.</p>
<p><strong>Free tier:</strong> Free trial, AI personalization, email sequences<br/>
<strong>Best for:</strong> Cold email outreach, personalization, outbound sales<br/>
<strong>Limits:</strong> Free trial only — no permanent free tier</p>
<p><a href="/tool/lemlist" class="btn-primary">View Lemlist Free Trial →</a></p>

<h2>8. Gong (No Free Tier) — Industry Benchmark for Revenue Intelligence</h2>
<p><strong>Rating: 4.6/5</strong></p>
<p>Gong is the industry benchmark for revenue intelligence, though it does not offer a free tier. It analyzes every sales call and meeting to uncover exactly what drives successful deals and what causes them to slip away. Gong's AI identifies objection patterns, competitive mentions, and deal risks from recorded conversations, providing actionable coaching insights for sales teams. Despite lacking a free option, Gong sets the standard that all other sales AI tools are measured against in terms of accuracy and depth. We include it here for comparison — its capabilities define what enterprise-level revenue intelligence looks like, making it a useful benchmark when evaluating free alternatives.</p>
<p><strong>Free tier:</strong> None<br/>
<strong>Best for:</strong> Revenue intelligence, deal analysis, sales coaching<br/>
<strong>Limits:</strong> No free tier — paid plans start at enterprise pricing</p>
<p><a href="/tool/gong" class="btn-primary">View Gong →</a></p>

<h2>9. Apollo.io (Free) — Best Sales Intelligence & Engagement</h2>
<p><strong>Rating: 4.4/5</strong></p>
<p>Apollo.io offers 10,000 free credits per month for lead generation and sales engagement on its robust free plan. It provides access to a massive B2B contact database with AI-driven search filters that narrow down prospects by industry, revenue, technology usage, and dozens of other criteria. The free tier includes email verification to ensure deliverability, sequence automation for multi-step outreach, and CRM integrations with HubSpot and Salesforce. Apollo.io's AI recommends the best contacts based on your ideal customer profile and predicts engagement likelihood. It's a powerful all-in-one sales intelligence and engagement platform that rivals paid tools in functionality.</p>
<p><strong>Free tier:</strong> 10,000 credits/month, AI recommendations, email verification<br/>
<strong>Best for:</strong> Sales intelligence, lead scoring, outreach automation<br/>
<strong>Limits:</strong> Credits reset monthly, limited export capacity</p>
<p><a href="/tool/apollo-io" class="btn-primary">View Apollo.io Free Tier →</a></p>

